<div class="row">
	<div class="column grid_4">
		<article>
			<h3>Live Ajax</h3>
			<p>
				This is a simple example on how to use the <em>viaAjax</em> method. The <em>viaAjax</em> method is used when ajax is called but you want the same controller/node/script to handle it.
				This works by detecting ajax and using the <em>viaAjax</em> method instead of the <em>execute</em> method from the same controller.
				It can be setup to use multiple different ajax calls to handle from the <em>viaAjax</em> method.
			</p>
			<p>
				<label>Live Search
					<input id="livesearch" type="text" name="livesearch">
				</label>
			</p>
		</article>
	</div>
</div>
